DataElement.preferredName: ARACNE Algorithm Programming Parameter Mutual Information Value Bin java.lang.Integer
DataElement.preferredDefinition: An information-theoretic algorithm for reverse engineering of transcriptional networks using microarray data, specifically designed to scale up to the complexity of regulatory networks in mammalian cells, yet general enough to address a wider range of network deconvolution problems, while eliminating the majority of indirect interactions inferred by co-expression methods.:A value that is passed to a routine._Expresses the extent to which the observed frequency of co-occurrence differs from that expected under the null hypothesis.:An interval into which a given data point does or does not fall._Generic value domain for a primitive java dataype that is an Integer (32-bit two's complement).
